Scaled_coord_XY (XY_NU) is Rock coords in Native Utits (integer Vector) Inp_Par_NU is parent size WH width-hieght in Native Units (integer Vector).
XY_NU = (Inp_Par_NU) * (Inp_Scale) * (1/Inp_Par_LU) As in Native units system of coords Y goes down, and in logic system of coors Y goes up: 0____x y | | LU y| NU 0 |___x
XY_NU: Xres = X, Yres = H - Y

Scaled_size_WH (WH_NU) is Rock size WH in Native Utits (integer Vector) Inp_Par_NU is parent size WH width-hieght in Native Units (integer Vector). Width of parent does not influence Rock size.
WH_NU = ([Const_Mtx] * [Inp_Par_NU]) * (Inp_Scale) * (1/Inp_Par_LU)
